a Sacra'' in the Middle Ages |title=Boethius: His Life, Thought, and Influence |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford |date=1981 |pp=214\u2013234 }}\n* {{citation |last=Historical Manuscripts Commission |date=1901 |ref={{harvid|HMC|1901}} |title=Report on Manuscripts in Various Collections, ''Vol.&nbsp;I'' Berwick-upon-Tweed, Burford, and Lostwithiel Corporations; the Counties of Wilts and Worcester; the Bishop of Chichester; and the Deans and Chapters of Chichester, Canterbury, and Salisbury |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GWcpAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover |location=London |publisher=Mackie &&nbsp;Co. for His Majesty's Stationery Office }}\n* {{citation |last=Holland |first=Richard A., Jr. |date=2012 |contribution=Anselm |contribution-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o3oNBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT42 |title=God, Time, and the Incarnation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o3oNBQAAQBAJ |pp=42\u201344 |isbn=978-1-61097-729-6 |location=Eugene |publisher=Wipf & Stock }}\n* {{citation |last=Hollister |first=C. Warren |year=1982 |title=Medieval Europe: A Short History |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |location=New York }}\n* {{citation |last=Hollister |first=C. Warren |year=1983 |title=The Making of England: 55 B.C. to 1399 |publisher=D. C. Heath and Company |location=Lexington  }}\n* {{citation |last=Hollister |first=C. Warren |date=2003 |title=Henry I |location=New Haven |publisher=Yale University Press |editor-last=Frost |editor-first=Amanda Clark |display-editors=0 |isbn=978-0-300-09829-7 }}\n* {{citation |last=Hughes-Edwards |first=Mari |title=Reading Medieval Anchoritism: Ideology and Spiritual Practices |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PFSuBwAAQBAJ |publisher=University of Wales Press |date=2012 |isbn=978-0-7083-2505-6 |location=Cardiff }}\n* {{citation |last=Janaro |first=John |url=https://www.anselm.edu/library/SAJ/pdf/32Janaro.pdf |title=Saint Anselm and the Development of the Doctrine of the Immaculate Conception: Historical and Theological Pe